Katie Hallsten

Hello! I am an orangutan conservationist and former primate cognition researcher who is now focused on supply chain sustainability and consulting.

My MSc project explores how a language-trained ape recognizes virtual objects representationally within virtual reality.

I hold a masters degree in Psychology from the University of St.Andrews and a bachelors degree in Cognitive and Behavioral Neuroscience from the University of California, San Diego.

My main hobbies include singing and baking, and I am always trying out new makeup techniques. Feel free to reach out!
